<h2>
  <a name="einsatzbereich"></a>
  Which information will I find under the category of “Deployment Area”?
</h2>
<p>
  <span lang="EN-US">The different areas in which the interviewees had to perform forced labor have been categorized into branches and economic sectors according to the criteria used in economic statistics.</span>
</p>
<p>
  <span lang="EN-US">The primary sector includes agriculture, agribusiness and forestry. The secondary sector encompasses mining and industry, crafts and trade, as well as construction, stonework and earthwork (including building construction and civil engineering as well as ore and stone extraction).<br/>The tertiary sector includes business/trade, healthcare, and transportation. Services in private households as well as for public employers (public sector) or in unspecified administration are also included here.</span>
</p>
<p>
  <span lang="EN-US">A separate group constitutes deployment by the Wehrmacht or Organisation Todt, in ports and shipyards and in camps (forced labor in concentration camps and death camps are listed separately).</span>
</p>
<p>
  <span lang="EN-US">The categories have been created according to the data available and have only been reviewed in individual cases. Places of deployment that could not be categorized come under the category “Miscellaneous”. In some cases, details are “Not Specified”.</span>
</p>
